item.title: CVE-2024-3660|2024-04-16T20:09:26.220Z -- tensorflow -- keras
item.description: A arbitrary code injection vulnerability in TensorFlow's Keras framework (<2.13) allows attackers to execute arbitrary code with the same permissions as the application using a model that allow arbitrary code irrespective of the application.
